1465  InstructionOperandConverter converter(this, instr);
1466  switch (type.representation()) {
1467  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1468  translations_.StoreFloatRegister(converter.ToFloatRegister(op));
1469  break;
1470  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1471  if (type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kHoleyFloat64) {
1472  translations_.StoreHoleyDoubleRegister(
1473  converter.ToDoubleRegister(op));
1474  } else {
1475  translations_.StoreDoubleRegister(converter.ToDoubleRegister(op));
1476  }
1477  break;
1478  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1479  translations_.StoreSimd128Register(converter.ToSimd128Register(op));
1480  break;
1481  default:
1482  UNREACHABLE();
1483  }
1484  } else {
1485  CHECK(op->IsImmediate());
1486  InstructionOperandConverter converter(this, instr);
1487  Constant constant = converter.ToConstant(op);
1488  DeoptimizationLiteral literal;
1489 
1490 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1491  if (info_->IsWasm() && v8_flags.wasm_deopt) {
1492  switch (type.representation()) {
1493  case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
1494  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToInt32());
1495  break;
1496  case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
1497  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToInt64());
1498  break;
1499  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1500  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToFloat32Safe());
1501  break;
1502  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1503  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(Float64(constant.ToFloat64()));
1504  break;
1505  case MachineRepresentation::kTagged: {
1506  DCHECK(!PointerCompressionIsEnabled() ||
1507  base::IsInRange(constant.ToInt64(), 0u, UINT32_MAX));
1508  Tagged<Smi> smi(static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64()));
1509  DCHECK(IsSmi(smi));
1510  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(smi);
1511  break;
1512  }
1513  default:
1514  UNIMPLEMENTED();
1515  }
1516  int literal_id = DefineDeoptimizationLiteral(literal);
1517  translations_.StoreLiteral(literal_id);
1518  return;
1519  }
1520 #endif
1521 
1522  switch (constant.type()) {
1523  case Constant::kInt32:
1524  if (type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kTagged) {
1525  // When pointers are 4 bytes, we can use int32 constants to represent
1526  // Smis.
1527  DCHECK_EQ(4, kSystemPointerSize);
1528  Tagged<Smi> smi(static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt32()));
1529  DCHECK(IsSmi(smi));
1530  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<double>(smi.value()));
1531  } else if (type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kBit) {
1532  if (constant.ToInt32() == 0) {
1533  literal =
1534  DeoptimizationLiteral(isolate()->factory()->false_value());
1535  } else {
1536  DCHECK_EQ(1, constant.ToInt32());
1537  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(isolate()->factory()->true_value());
1538  }
1539  } else {
1540  DCHECK(type == MachineType::Int32() ||
1541  type == MachineType::Uint32() ||
1542  type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32 ||
1543  type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kNone);
1544  DCHECK(type.representation() != MachineRepresentation::kNone ||
1545  constant.ToInt32() == FrameStateDescriptor::kImpossibleValue);
1546  if (type == MachineType::Uint32()) {
1547  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(
1548  static_cast<double>(static_cast<uint32_t>(constant.ToInt32())));
1549  } else {
1550  literal =
1551  DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<double>(constant.ToInt32()));
1552  }
1553  }
1554  break;
1555  case Constant::kInt64:
1556  DCHECK_EQ(8, kSystemPointerSize);
1557  if (type == MachineType::SignedBigInt64()) {
1558  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToInt64());
1559  } else if (type == MachineType::UnsignedBigInt64()) {
1560  literal =
1561  DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<uint64_t>(constant.ToInt64()));
1562  } else if (type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1563  // TODO(nicohartmann@, chromium:41497374): Disabling this CHECK
1564  // because we can see cases where this is violated in unreachable
1565  // code. We should re-enable once we have an idea on how to prevent
1566  // this from happening.
1567  // CHECK_EQ(
1568  // constant.ToInt64(),
1569  // static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<double>(constant.ToInt64())));
1570  literal =
1571  DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<double>(constant.ToInt64()));
1572  } else {
1573  // When pointers are 8 bytes, we can use int64 constants to represent
1574  // Smis.
1575  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, type.representation());
1576  Tagged<Smi> smi(static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64()));
1577  DCHECK(IsSmi(smi));
1578  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<double>(smi.value()));
1579  }
1580  break;
1581  case Constant::kFloat32:
1582  DCHECK(type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32 ||
1583  type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1584  literal =
1585  DeoptimizationLiteral(static_cast<double>(constant.ToFloat32()));
1586  break;
1587  case Constant::kFloat64:
1588  DCHECK(type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64 ||
1589  type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1590  if (type == MachineType::HoleyFloat64() &&
1591  constant.ToFloat64().AsUint64() == kHoleNanInt64) {
1592  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral::HoleNaN();
1593  } else {
1594  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToFloat64().value());
1595  }
1596  break;
1597  case Constant::kHeapObject:
1598  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, type.representation());
1599  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToHeapObject());
1600  break;
1601  case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject:
1602  DCHECK_EQ(MachineType::AnyTagged(), type);
1603  literal = DeoptimizationLiteral(constant.ToHeapObject());
1604  break;
1605  default:
1606  UNREACHABLE();
1607  }
1608  if (literal.object().equals(info()->closure()) &&
1609  info()->function_context_specializing()) {
1610  translations_.StoreJSFrameFunction();
1611  } else {
1612  int literal_id = DefineDeoptimizationLiteral(literal);
1613  translations_.StoreLiteral(literal_id);
1614  }
1615  }

1219  CpuFeatureScope scope(masm(), ARMv7);
1220  __ rbit(i.OutputRegister(), i.InputRegister(0));
1221  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1222  break;
1223  }

1225  __ rev(i.OutputRegister(), i.InputRegister(0));
1226  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1227  break;

1229  __ clz(i.OutputRegister(), i.InputRegister(0));
1230  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1231  break;

1233  __ cmp(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputOperand2(1));
1234  DCHECK_EQ(SetCC, i.OutputSBit());
1235  break;

1237  __ cmn(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputOperand2(1));

1239  break;

1243  break;

1245  __ teq(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputOperand2(1));
1246  DCHECK_EQ(SetCC, i.OutputSBit());
1247  break;
1248  case kArmAddPair:
1249  // i.InputRegister(0) ... left low word.
1250  // i.InputRegister(1) ... left high word.
1251  // i.InputRegister(2) ... right low word.
1252  // i.InputRegister(3) ... right high word.
1253  __ add(i.OutputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(2),
1254  SetCC);
1255  __ adc(i.OutputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(1),
1256  Operand(i.InputRegister(3)));
1257  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1258  break;
1259  case kArmSubPair:
1260  // i.InputRegister(0) ... left low word.
1261  // i.InputRegister(1) ... left high word.
1262  // i.InputRegister(2) ... right low word.
1263  // i.InputRegister(3) ... right high word.
1264  __ sub(i.OutputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(2),
1265  SetCC);
1266  __ sbc(i.OutputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(1),
1267  Operand(i.InputRegister(3)));
1268  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1269  break;
1270  case kArmMulPair:
1271  // i.InputRegister(0) ... left low word.
1272  // i.InputRegister(1) ... left high word.
1273  // i.InputRegister(2) ... right low word.
1274  // i.InputRegister(3) ... right high word.
1275  __ umull(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(0),
1276  i.InputRegister(2));
1277  __ mla(i.OutputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(3),
1278  i.OutputRegister(1));
1279  __ mla(i.OutputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2), i.InputRegister(1),
1280  i.OutputRegister(1));
1281  break;
1282  case kArmLslPair: {
1283  Register second_output =
1284  instr->OutputCount() >= 2 ? i.OutputRegister(1) : i.TempRegister(0);
1285  if (instr->InputAt(2)->IsImmediate()) {
1286  __ LslPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1287  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputInt32(2));
1288  } else {
1289  __ LslPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1290  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2));
1291  }
1292  break;
1293  }
1294  case kArmLsrPair: {
1295  Register second_output =
1296  instr->OutputCount() >= 2 ? i.OutputRegister(1) : i.TempRegister(0);
1297  if (instr->InputAt(2)->IsImmediate()) {
1298  __ LsrPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1299  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputInt32(2));
1300  } else {
1301  __ LsrPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1302  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2));
1303  }
1304  break;
1305  }
1306  case kArmAsrPair: {
1307  Register second_output =
1308  instr->OutputCount() >= 2 ? i.OutputRegister(1) : i.TempRegister(0);
1309  if (instr->InputAt(2)->IsImmediate()) {
1310  __ AsrPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1311  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputInt32(2));
1312  } else {
1313  __ AsrPair(i.OutputRegister(0), second_output, i.InputRegister(0),
1314  i.InputRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2));
1315  }
1316  break;
1317  }
1318  case kArmVcmpF32:
1319  if (instr->InputAt(1)->IsFPRegister()) {
1320  __ VFPCompareAndSetFlags(i.InputFloatRegister(0),
1321  i.InputFloatRegister(1));
1322  } else {

1324  // 0.0 is the only immediate supported by vcmp instructions.

1326  __ VFPCompareAndSetFlags(i.InputFloatRegister(0), i.InputFloat32(1));
1327  }

1751  }
1752  case kArmPush: {
1753  int stack_decrement = i.InputInt32(0);
1754  int slots = stack_decrement / kSystemPointerSize;
1755  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(instr->InputAt(1));
1756  MachineRepresentation rep = op->representation();
1757  int pushed_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
1758  // Slot-sized arguments are never padded but there may be a gap if
1759  // the slot allocator reclaimed other padding slots. Adjust the stack
1760  // here to skip any gap.
1761  __ AllocateStackSpace((slots - pushed_slots) * kSystemPointerSize);
1762  switch (rep) {
1763  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1764  __ vpush(i.InputFloatRegister(1));
1765  break;
1766  case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1767  __ vpush(i.InputDoubleRegister(1));
1768  break;
1769  case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
1770  __ vpush(i.InputSimd128Register(1));
1771  break;
1772  default:
1773  __ push(i.InputRegister(1));
1774  break;
1775  }
1776  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(slots);
1777  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1778  break;
1779  }
1780  case kArmPoke: {
1781  int const slot = MiscField::decode(instr->opcode());
1782  __ str(i.InputRegister(0), MemOperand(sp, slot * kSystemPointerSize));
1783  DCHECK_EQ(LeaveCC, i.OutputSBit());
1784  break;
1785  }
1786  case kArmPeek: {
1787  int reverse_slot = i.InputInt32(0);
1788  int offset =
1789  FrameSlotToFPOffset(frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - reverse_slot);
1790  if (instr->OutputAt(0)->IsFPRegister()) {
1791  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(instr->OutputAt(0));
1792  if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
1793  __ vldr(i.OutputDoubleRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1794  } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
1795  __ vldr(i.OutputFloatRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1796  } else {
1797  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
1798  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
1799  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1800  __ add(scratch, fp, Operand(offset));
1801  __ vld1(Neon8, NeonListOperand(i.OutputSimd128Register()),
1802  NeonMemOperand(scratch));
1803  }
1804  } else {
1805  __ ldr(i.OutputRegister(), MemOperand(fp, offset));
1806  }
1807  break;
1808  }

1810  __ dmb(ISH);
1811  break;
1812  }

2117  case kArmI64x2Mul: {
2118  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
2119  QwNeonRegister dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
2120  QwNeonRegister left = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
2121  QwNeonRegister right = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
2122  QwNeonRegister tmp1 = i.TempSimd128Register(0);
2123  QwNeonRegister tmp2 = temps.AcquireQ();
2124 
2125  // This algorithm uses vector operations to perform 64-bit integer
2126  // multiplication by splitting it into a high and low 32-bit integers.
2127  // The tricky part is getting the low and high integers in the correct
2128  // place inside a NEON register, so that we can use as little vmull and
2129  // vmlal as possible.
2130 
2131  // Move left and right into temporaries, they will be modified by vtrn.
2132  __ vmov(tmp1, left);
2133  __ vmov(tmp2, right);
2134 
2135  // This diagram shows how the 64-bit integers fit into NEON registers.
2136  //
2137  // [q.high()| q.low()]
2138  // left/tmp1: [ a3, a2 | a1, a0 ]
2139  // right/tmp2: [ b3, b2 | b1, b0 ]
2140  //
2141  // We want to multiply the low 32 bits of left with high 32 bits of right,
2142  // for each lane, i.e. a2 * b3, a0 * b1. However, vmull takes two input d
2143  // registers, and multiply the corresponding low/high 32 bits, to get a
2144  // 64-bit integer: a1 * b1, a0 * b0. In order to make it work we transpose
2145  // the vectors, so that we get the low 32 bits of each 64-bit integer into
2146  // the same lane, similarly for high 32 bits.
2147  __ vtrn(Neon32, tmp1.low(), tmp1.high());
2148  // tmp1: [ a3, a1 | a2, a0 ]
2149  __ vtrn(Neon32, tmp2.low(), tmp2.high());
2150  // tmp2: [ b3, b1 | b2, b0 ]
2151 
2152  __ vmull(NeonU32, dst, tmp1.low(), tmp2.high());
2153  // dst: [ a2*b3 | a0*b1 ]
2154  __ vmlal(NeonU32, dst, tmp1.high(), tmp2.low());
2155  // dst: [ a2*b3 + a3*b2 | a0*b1 + a1*b0 ]
2156  __ vshl(NeonU64, dst, dst, 32);
2157  // dst: [ (a2*b3 + a3*b2) << 32 | (a0*b1 + a1*b0) << 32 ]
2158 
2159  __ vmlal(NeonU32, dst, tmp1.low(), tmp2.low());
2160  // dst: [ (a2*b3 + a3*b2)<<32 + (a2*b2) | (a0*b1 + a1*b0)<<32 + (a0*b0) ]
2161  break;
2162  }
2163  case kArmI64x2Abs: {
2164  __ I64x2Abs(i.OutputSimd128Register(), i.InputSimd128Register(0));
2165  break;
2166  }
2167  case kArmI64x2Neg: {
2168  Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register();
2169  __ vmov(dst, uint64_t{0});
2170  __ vsub(Neon64, dst, dst, i.InputSimd128Register(0));
2171  break;
2172  }

2181  break;

2245  case kArmF32x4Sqrt: {

2247  QwNeonRegister src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(0);
2248  DCHECK_EQ(dst, q0);
2249  DCHECK_EQ(src1, q0);
2250 #define S_FROM_Q(reg, lane) SwVfpRegister::from_code(reg.code() * 4 + lane)
2251  __ vsqrt(S_FROM_Q(dst, 0), S_FROM_Q(src1, 0));
2252  __ vsqrt(S_FROM_Q(dst, 1), S_FROM_Q(src1, 1));
2253  __ vsqrt(S_FROM_Q(dst, 2), S_FROM_Q(src1, 2));
2254  __ vsqrt(S_FROM_Q(dst, 3), S_FROM_Q(src1, 3));

2520  Simd128Register mask = i.TempSimd128Register(0);
2521

2523  // Set i-th bit of each lane i. When AND with tmp, the lanes that

2528  __ vpadd(Neon32, tmp.low(), tmp.low(), tmp.high());

2530  __ VmovLow(dst, tmp.low());

2902  Register dst = i.OutputRegister();

2904  Simd128Register tmp = temps.AcquireQ();
2905  Simd128Register mask = i.TempSimd128Register(0);
2906

2908  // Set i-th bit of each lane i. When AND with tmp, the lanes that
2909  // are signed will have i-th bit set, unsigned will be 0.

3031  case kArmS32x4Shuffle: {
3032  Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register(),
3033  src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0),
3034  src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
3035  DCHECK_NE(dst, src0);
3036  DCHECK_NE(dst, src1);
3037  // Perform shuffle as a vmov per lane.
3038  int dst_code = dst.code() * 4;
3039  int src0_code = src0.code() * 4;
3040  int src1_code = src1.code() * 4;
3041  int32_t shuffle = i.InputInt32(2);
3042  for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3043  int lane = shuffle & 0x7;
3044  int src_code = src0_code;
3045  if (lane >= 4) {
3046  src_code = src1_code;
3047  lane &= 0x3;
3048  }
3049  __ VmovExtended(dst_code + i, src_code + lane);
3050  shuffle >>= 8;
3051  }
3052  break;
3053  }

3194  case kArmI8x16Swizzle: {
3195  Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register(),
3196  tbl = i.InputSimd128Register(0),
3197  src = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
3198  NeonListOperand table(tbl);
3199  __ vtbl(dst.low(), table, src.low());
3200  __ vtbl(dst.high(), table, src.high());
3201  break;
3202  }
3203  case kArmI8x16Shuffle: {
3204  Simd128Register dst = i.OutputSimd128Register(),
3205  src0 = i.InputSimd128Register(0),
3206  src1 = i.InputSimd128Register(1);
3207  DwVfpRegister table_base = src0.low();
3208  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(masm());
3209  Simd128Register scratch = temps.AcquireQ();
3210  // If unary shuffle, table is src0 (2 d-registers), otherwise src0 and
3211  // src1. They must be consecutive.
3212  int table_size = src0 == src1 ? 2 : 4;
3213  DCHECK_IMPLIES(src0 != src1, src0.code() + 1 == src1.code());
3214  // The shuffle lane mask is a byte mask, materialize in scratch.
3215  int scratch_s_base = scratch.code() * 4;
3216  for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
3217  uint32_t four_lanes = i.InputUint32(2 + j);
3218  DCHECK_EQ(0, four_lanes & (table_size == 2 ? 0xF0F0F0F0 : 0xE0E0E0E0));
3219  __ vmov(SwVfpRegister::from_code(scratch_s_base + j),
3220  Float32::FromBits(four_lanes));
3221  }
3222  NeonListOperand table(table_base, table_size);
3223  if (dst != src0 && dst != src1) {
3224  __ vtbl(dst.low(), table, scratch.low());
3225  __ vtbl(dst.high(), table, scratch.high());
3226  } else {
3227  __ vtbl(scratch.low(), table, scratch.low());
3228  __ vtbl(scratch.high(), table, scratch.high());
3229  __ vmov(dst, scratch);
3230  }
3231  break;

3451  case kAtomicExchangeWithWriteBarrier: {

3497 #define ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(op, inst) \
3498  case kAtomic##op##Int8: \
3499  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(ldrexb, strexb, inst); \
3500  __ sxtb(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(0)); \
3501  break; \
3502  case kAtomic##op##Uint8: \
3503  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(ldrexb, strexb, inst); \
3504  break; \
3505  case kAtomic##op##Int16: \
3506  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(ldrexh, strexh, inst); \
3507  __ sxth(i.OutputRegister(0), i.OutputRegister(0)); \
3508  break; \
3509  case kAtomic##op##Uint16: \
3510  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(ldrexh, strexh, inst); \
3511  break; \
3512  case kAtomic##op##Word32: \
3513  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP(ldrex, strex, inst); \
3514  break;
3515  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Add, add)
3516  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Sub, sub)
3517  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(And, and_)
3518  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, orr)
3519  ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, eor)
3520 #undef ATOMIC_BINOP_CASE
3521  case kArmWord32AtomicPairLoad: {
3522  if (instr->OutputCount() == 2) {
3523  DCHECK(VerifyOutputOfAtomicPairInstr(&i, instr, r0, r1));
3524  __ add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1));
3525  __ ldrexd(r0, r1, i.TempRegister(0));
3526  __ dmb(ISH);
3527  } else {
3528  // A special case of this instruction: even though this is a pair load,
3529  // we only need one of the two words. We emit a normal atomic load.
3530  DCHECK_EQ(instr->OutputCount(), 1);
3531  Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
3532  Register offset = i.InputRegister(1);
3533  DCHECK(instr->InputAt(2)->IsImmediate());
3534  int32_t offset_imm = i.InputInt32(2);
3535  if (offset_imm != 0) {
3536  Register temp = i.TempRegister(0);
3537  __ add(temp, offset, Operand(offset_imm));
3538  offset = temp;
3539  }
3540  __ ldr(i.OutputRegister(), MemOperand(base, offset));
3541  __ dmb(ISH);
3542  }
3543  break;
3544  }
3545  case kArmWord32AtomicPairStore: {
3546  Label store;
3547  Register base = i.InputRegister(0);
3548  Register offset = i.InputRegister(1);
3549  Register value_low = i.InputRegister(2);
3550  Register value_high = i.InputRegister(3);
3551  Register actual_addr = i.TempRegister(0);
3552  // The {ldrexd} instruction needs two temp registers. We do not need the
3553  // result of {ldrexd}, but {strexd} likely fails without the {ldrexd}.
3554  Register tmp1 = i.TempRegister(1);
3555  Register tmp2 = i.TempRegister(2);
3556  // Reuse one of the temp registers for the result of {strexd}.
3557  Register store_result = tmp1;
3558  __ add(actual_addr, base, offset);
3559  __ dmb(ISH);
3560  __ bind(&store);
3561  // Add this {ldrexd} instruction here so that {strexd} below can succeed.
3562  // We don't need the result of {ldrexd} itself.
3563  __ ldrexd(tmp1, tmp2, actual_addr);
3564  __ strexd(store_result, value_low, value_high, actual_addr);
3565  __ cmp(store_result, Operand(0));
3566  __ b(ne, &store);
3567  __ dmb(ISH);
3568  break;
3569  }
3570 #define ATOMIC_ARITH_BINOP_CASE(op, instr1, instr2) \
3571  case kArmWord32AtomicPair##op: { \
3572  DCHECK(VerifyOutputOfAtomicPairInstr(&i, instr, r2, r3)); \
3573  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC64_ARITH_BINOP(instr1, instr2); \
3574  break; \
3575  }
3576  ATOMIC_ARITH_BINOP_CASE(Add, add, adc)
3577  ATOMIC_ARITH_BINOP_CASE(Sub, sub, sbc)
3578 #undef ATOMIC_ARITH_BINOP_CASE
3579 #define ATOMIC_LOGIC_BINOP_CASE(op, instr1) \
3580  case kArmWord32AtomicPair##op: { \
3581  DCHECK(VerifyOutputOfAtomicPairInstr(&i, instr, r2, r3)); \
3582  ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC64_LOGIC_BINOP(instr1); \
3583  break; \
3584  }
3585  ATOMIC_LOGIC_BINOP_CASE(And, and_)
3586  ATOMIC_LOGIC_BINOP_CASE(Or, orr)
3587  ATOMIC_LOGIC_BINOP_CASE(Xor, eor)
3588 #undef ATOMIC_LOGIC_BINOP_CASE
3589  case kArmWord32AtomicPairExchange: {
3590  DCHECK(VerifyOutputOfAtomicPairInstr(&i, instr, r6, r7));
3591  Label exchange;
3592  __ add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(2), i.InputRegister(3));
3593  __ dmb(ISH);
3594  __ bind(&exchange);
3595  __ ldrexd(r6, r7, i.TempRegister(0));
3596  __ strexd(i.TempRegister(1), i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1),
3597  i.TempRegister(0));
3598  __ teq(i.TempRegister(1), Operand(0));
3599  __ b(ne, &exchange);
3600  __ dmb(ISH);
3601  break;
3602  }
3603  case kArmWord32AtomicPairCompareExchange: {
3604  DCHECK(VerifyOutputOfAtomicPairInstr(&i, instr, r2, r3));
3605  __ add(i.TempRegister(0), i.InputRegister(4), i.InputRegister(5));
3606  Label compareExchange;
3607  Label exit;
3608  __ dmb(ISH);
3609  __ bind(&compareExchange);
3610  __ ldrexd(r2, r3, i.TempRegister(0));
3611  __ teq(i.InputRegister(0), Operand(r2));
3612  __ b(ne, &exit);
3613  __ teq(i.InputRegister(1), Operand(r3));
3614  __ b(ne, &exit);
3615  __ strexd(i.TempRegister(1), i.InputRegister(2), i.InputRegister(3),
3616  i.TempRegister(0));
3617  __ teq(i.TempRegister(1), Operand(0));
3618  __ b(ne, &compareExchange);
3619  __ bind(&exit);
3620  __ dmb(ISH);
3621  break;
3622  }
3623 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_LOAD_INTEGER
3624 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_STORE_INTEGER
3625 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_INTEGER
3626 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_INTEGER
3627 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC_BINOP
3628 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC64_ARITH_BINOP
3629 #undef ASSEMBLE_ATOMIC64_LOGIC_BINOP
3630 #undef ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_BINOP
3631 #undef ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP
3632 #undef ASSEMBLE_NEON_NARROWING_OP
3633 #undef ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_LEFT
3634 #undef ASSEMBLE_SIMD_SHIFT_RIGHT
3635  }
3636  return kSuccess;
